                     <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177109110021"></xptr>THE WHOLE PROCEEDINGS ON THE King's Commission of the Peace, Oyer and Terminer, and Gaol-Delivery FOR THE CITY of LONDON; And also the Gaol-Delivery for the County of MIDDLESEX; HELD AT JUSTICE-HALL in the OLD-BAILEY, On Wednesday the 11th, Thursday the 12th, Friday the 13th, Saturday the 14th, Monday the 16th, Tuesday the 17th, Wednesday the 18th, Thursday the 19th, Friday the 20th, Saturday the 21st, Monday the 23d, and Tuesday the 24th of September, 1771.</p>
                  <p>In the Eleventh Year of His MAJESTY's Reign. Being the Seventh SESSION in the MAYORALTY of The Right Honourable BRASS CROSBY, Esq; LORD-MAYOR of the CITY of LONDON.</p>
                  <p>NUMBER VII. PART II.</p>
                  <p>LONDON:</p>
                  <p>Sold by T. EVANS, No. 54, in PATER-NOSTER ROW.</p>
